        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50164",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This looks kinda old. Evan, didn't we switch to \\GlobIterator for that reason?\r\n\r\nBy the way, Yonni, did you test with the current beta3 or an old version?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-03-29T10:02:22.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-03-29T10:04:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50167",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yonman",
                        "name": "yonman",
                        "displayName": "Yonni Mendes",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Forked SkeletonApplication and Zf2 and sent pull requests:\r\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/zendframework\/ZendSkeletonApplication\/pull\/49\r\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/zendframework\/zf2\/pull\/980",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yonman",
                        "name": "yonman",
                        "displayName": "Yonni Mendes",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-03-29T13:59:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-03-29T13:59:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50168",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yonman",
                        "name": "yonman",
                        "displayName": "Yonni Mendes",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Tested with beta3, found a TODO in ConfigListener so I took it up with Matthew. According to him globiterators were inapplicable, so I applied a simpler solution.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yonman",
                        "name": "yonman",
                        "displayName": "Yonni Mendes",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-03-29T14:00:32.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-03-29T14:01:09.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50169",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=evan.pro",
                        "name": "evan.pro",
                        "displayName": "Evan Coury",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I had discussed this with Matthew and others on IRC. We discovered that \\GlobIterator didn't solve the issue like we had anticipated it would (it doesn't support GLOB_BRACE at all, actually).\r\n\r\nIIRC, Matthew was thinking GLOB_BRACE wouldn't work on Windows, but it turns out it does. It seems to only be non-GNU systems like Solaris that don't support it and I think the consensus was that people on those systems can easily change the glob pattern (and we could document such). Though, I'm unsure if passing GLOB_BRACE as a flag throws a warning or anything on non-GNU systems. Anyway, I suppose I don't mind changing this to two globs though simply to maintain a higher level of compatibility if there's no objections.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=evan.pro",
                        "name": "evan.pro",
                        "displayName": "Evan Coury",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-03-29T14:07:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-03-29T14:07:10.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50170",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I could come up with a fallback solution so GLOB_BRACE can still be used, even on non-GNU systems.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-03-29T14:08:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-03-29T14:08:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50189",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yonman",
                        "name": "yonman",
                        "displayName": "Yonni Mendes",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "One more problematic point:\r\nAIX glob calls seem to ignore cwd - I can only get correct results when we use an absolute path.\r\nWhen testing, I verified with getcwd that we are in the document root, etc...",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yonman",
                        "name": "yonman",
                        "displayName": "Yonni Mendes",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-04-01T12:05:51.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-04-01T12:05:51.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50293",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=evan.pro",
                        "name": "evan.pro",
                        "displayName": "Evan Coury",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm not really sure there's much we can do to fix the AIX glob cwd issue...\r\n\r\nIt would seem to me that there are three options in this case:\r\n\r\n1) Simply adjust the glob paths to be absolute after cloning the skeleton.\r\n2) Use Zend\\Module\\Listener\\ConfigListener::addConfigStaticPaths() to add each config file explicitly instead of addConfigGlobPaths() to add glob patterns.\r\n3) Re-implement glob() completely in PHP, which I'd prefer we not do.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=evan.pro",
                        "name": "evan.pro",
                        "displayName": "Evan Coury",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-04-13T10:35:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-05-30T21:58:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50902",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=evan.pro",
                        "name": "evan.pro",
                        "displayName": "Evan Coury",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This issue is resolved via [PR 983|https:\/\/github.com\/zendframework\/zf2\/pull\/983] and [PR 1419|https:\/\/github.com\/zendframework\/zf2\/pull\/1419].",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=evan.pro",
                        "name": "evan.pro",
                        "displayName": "Evan Coury",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-05-31T15:34:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-05-31T15:34:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51197",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yonman",
                        "name": "yonman",
                        "displayName": "Yonni Mendes",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The fix in PR 983 seem to work when I tested it in our IBMi machine but I had to create absolute paths for it to work. It seems that AIX glob works only with static paths - otherwise you get empty results and an empty configuration.\r\n\r\nShould this issue be reopened for this? or should I create a new issue?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yonman",
                        "name": "yonman",
                        "displayName": "Yonni Mendes",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-06-24T15:11:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-06-24T15:11:10.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51221",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=evan.pro",
                        "name": "evan.pro",
                        "displayName": "Evan Coury",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm re-opening and assigning to Ben Scholzen. Perhaps there is something he can add to our Zend\\Stdlib\\Glob class to account for this.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=evan.pro",
                        "name": "evan.pro",
                        "displayName": "Evan Coury",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-06-28T06:19:36.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-06-28T06:19:36.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/52084",
                    "author": {
